<taxonomicName authority="Yoshitomi &amp; Ruta, 2010" authorityName="Yoshitomi &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2010" box="[738,957,1072,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schawalleroides" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[738,957,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">S. schawalleroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[965,1030,1072,1098]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); parameres distinctly curved dorsally; apical part of penis long, deeply excised at apex.
</paragraph>
